title: Getting Started
description: The Getting Started section starts with a list of the Traxidy Areas, each one with a link to a short video which provides a guided tour of each Area.

title: Traxidy Overview
description: Learn how Traxidy can help from Plan Development to Project Close.

title: Navigation & Key Terms
description: Key Areas and terms to know when navigating within Traxidy.

title: Orientation: The Basics
description: Helpful tips and options to easily view, sort, and edit your project information.

title: Account Settings
description: Learn how to set up and tailor settings for your membership account.

title: Project Settings
description: Learn how to set up and tailor your settings for each project.

title: Dashboard
description: The Dashboard Area is always your starting point to view project priorities and to access a Project and itâ€™s Project Areas.

title: Start a New Project
description: You can start a New Project from either the Dashboard or the Main Menu.

title: Project Information
description: The one place to view and update all your project details including key dates, deliverables, budget, and more.

title: Working with Contacts
description: Create and add individual contacts to your project, give them collaboration access and connect them to meetings.

title: Setting-Up Project Meetings
description: Set up your project meetings in Traxidy and easily record each one and save time confirming attendance and creating Meeting Minutes.

title: Create Meeting Minutes
description: From the Traxidy Project Meetings Area, you can easily create, save and send Meeting Minutes to Project Team Members.

title: Recording Actions Issues Decisions (AID)
description: AID is your Traxidy Area to easily record, track and manage all project work, details, and updates related to Actions, Issues and Decisions.

title: Record & Manage Risks
description: The Traxidy Risks Area is used to record, track, manage and prioritize Project Risks.

title: Constraints Green Yellow Red (GYR)
description: The Traxidy Area to assess, report and visually track the status of the overall project and key project constraints.

title: Using Project Status
description: It is easy to create, tailor, present and report real-time Project Status.

title: Using the High-Level (HL) Plan
description: The High-Level (HL) Plan provides a visual, simplified project plan, timeframe and schedule.

title: Manage Changes
description: Changes is the Traxidy Area to record, track and manage all potential project changes from investigation to approval.

title: Create a Change Request Form
description: An Automated Change Request Form making it easier to submit and review changes.

title: Learn & Improve / Project Learnings
description: Easily capture and keep track of your notes and record learnings and ideas throughout the project.

title: Reports & Forms
description: Learn about Traxidy project area reports and forms and ways to present, save, print and send.

title: Closed Projects
description: One Area to access and reference all your Closed Project details.

title: All Contacts
description: A complete listing of all contacts across all of your projects in Traxidy.

title: All Learnings
description: A full record of all learnings and notes across all projects in Traxidy.

title: Using the Feedback Area
description: Let us know how we can make Traxidy even better.

title: Rewards
description: Share Traxidy with a colleague or friend and earn rewards.

title: Collaboration
description: Granting Contacts access to projects as CONTRIBUTOR or REVIEWER.

title: If Your Trial or Account Expires
description: What you can do if your Free Trial expires.

title: Multi-Client Status Reporting
description: One app but with the ability to present project portfolios and status to any number of different clients
